name: AC35 Magnetic Drill Press
description:
• Weighs 23 lbs
• Magnetic Strength 2,200 lbs
• Cutter capacity: 1-3/8" diameter x 2" depth
• Standard external fluid reservoir
• Quick change cutter arbor
• 1 Speed Motor:  600 RPM
• Easy to maneuver
• Same capacity as machines weighing much more
• Convenient cooling and less fill ups than arbor reservoir
• Annular cutters changed quickly for use with twist drills
• Great for use with carbide tipped annular cutters
• Includes safety chain
• AC35 Manual is available in Technical Support and Literature Section on this website


• Click here for the 


AC35 User Manual
short_description: Lightweight, powerful and economical magnetic drill press with a high torque motor.Includes carry case, quick-release cutter arbor, external coolant bottle, safety guard, drift key and hex keys.
summary: Weight: 23 lbs.Magnetic Strength:  2,200 lbsMotor:  1,200 WattMotor Speed:  600 RPMCutter Capacity:  1-3/8"Drill Capacity:  1/2"Depth of Cut:  2"

name: 1" Carbide Tipped Hole Cutter
description: 1" Carbide Tipped Hole Cutter
short_description:
Deliver "more holes per charge" in battery-powered drills 
 Cut thin materials, including stainless steel, quickly and smoothly
 1/4" Hex Shank for use in QCD (quick-change driver)
 Thin wall construction and three carbide tips for fast drilling 
and reduced drag
summary: Special tungsten carbide teethExcellent wear and heat resistanceCuts stainless steel and tough alloysEjector Spring ejects the slug, saving time1/4" hex shank: no assembly required and stable accurate drillingSafety Collar Stop: Prevents over penetration for safer faster operation
size_info: Champion Cutting Tools - 1" Carbide Tipped Hole Cutter

name: XLUB FLUID 16OZ
Group_Name: Brute Lube Cutting Fluid - Champion Cutting Tools
description:
16oz Bottle of XLUB Fluid.
Multipurpose cutting and tapping fluid specially formulated to extend tool life and reduce chip welding. Provides a precision finish with closer tolerances on finished work. Complies with OSHA regulations and contains no 1,1,1 Trichloroethane. Formulated to cling to tools for a continuous shield against friction and heat.

performance of any portable magnetic

name: Mechanics Length Drills
Group_Name: Champion Cutting Tools - Mechanics Length Drills
description: 1/16" Mechanics Length Drill
short_description:
Description: Strong, rigid overall
length.Heavy duty 135° split point for
self-centering and quick penetration.
Heavy duty web geometry provides
added rigidity.The three flatted shank
design ensures positive grip in keyless
drill chucks. 
Applications:Ideal for the aircraft
industry. Used for the drilling of high
tensile martensitic stainless steels,
titanium alloys and hard steel.

description: 7/16" Mechanics Length Drill
short_description:
Description: Strong, rigid overall
length.Heavy duty 135° split point for
self-centering and quick penetration.
Heavy duty web geometry provides
added rigidity.The three flatted shank
design ensures positive grip in keyless
drill chucks. 
Applications:Ideal for the aircraft
industry. Used for the drilling of high
tensile martensitic stainless steels,
titanium alloys and hard steel.
summary: EDP No./Diameter: 7/16"Decimal Equivalent:.4375Flute Length: 2-15/16Overall Length: 4-1/2Note: 3/8 thru 1/2 have 3/8" diameter flatted shanks.

category_names: Taps|Straight Shank - Metal Drill Bits|Drill Bit and Tap Sets
name: Combination Pack Tap & Drill 6-32 Tap & #36 Bit
Group_Name: Champion Cutting Tools Combination Pack Taps & Drills
meta_title: Combination Pack Tap & Drill 6-32 Tap & #36 Bit
small_image_label: Combination Pack Tap & Drill 6-32 Tap & #36 Bit
thumbnail_label: Combination Pack Tap & Drill 6-32 Tap & #36 Bit
short_description:
308 High Speed Hand Tap
High quality high speed steel hand taps can be operated in tap wrenches or production tapping heads. Supplied in standard "H" limits that provide a proper class of fit for most threading applications. 

Brute Platinum XL5
Unique web geometry, especially useful
in portable drilling of stainless steel, titanium alloys,
and other hard-to-drill materials.
summary:
Create new threads and clean up damaged threads. Achieve close tolerances for safe, secure fastening. A range of sizes are available from
machine screw 6-32 to 1/2-13. HSS hand taps are plug chamfered with 3-5 threads for easy starting. Champion high speed steel hand taps
(Series #308) are professional grade threading tools. The iPac solution matches each tap with the correct twist drill. No more time wasted
searching for the right size twist drill. With iPac the drill and tap are perfectly matched every time
meta_keyword: Combination Pack Tap & Drill 6-32 Tap & #36 Bit

name: CM95 SDS Stop Bits
description:
Designed to work with the most popular sizes of drop-in anchors. CM95-Stop Bits provide a controlled drilling depth in concrete and masonry. They eliminate guesswork, and the unnecessary wrapping of tape around drills.
A versatile tool in masonry applications from installing cable trays and struts, to suspending conduit in electrical and air sytems to pipe support and suspended lighting, stadium seating and much more.
• Large diameter stop collar/ring avoids over penetration into concrete
• Flute extends all the way to an undercut stop ring enhancing dust extraction
• Centering tip for quicker spot drilling • Carbide Tip SDS Plus Shank
• Sizes range from 3/8-5/8” • Works with anchors from 1/4-1/2”

name: Champion 1" Carbide Tipped Hole Cutter
description: An extremely productive tool that is a cost effective alternative to bi-metal holesaws for drilling holes in steel and other materials up to 1" thick.
short_description: The perfect portable tool for the professional electrician, plumber, mechanic and general contractor. Productive tool that is a cost effective alternative to bi-metal holesawsFor cutting steel plate, iron, aluminum, copper, cast iron, stainless steel, FRP (i.e. fiberglass) and plastics up to 1" thick9/16" to 3" have 3" shank, 3-1/4" to 4-1/2" have 1/2" shank
summary: Special tungsten carbide teethExcellent wear and heat resistanceCuts stainless steel and tough alloysOne piece constructionNo assembly requiredStable accurate drillingStandard ejector springEjects the slug, saving timeSafety collar stopPrevents over penetration for safer, faster operationChampion CT7 hole cutters feature two sets of three cutting blades, each with different geometries. This unique system balances the cutting forces enabling rapid, smooth drilling with better control.

name: CHAMPION 06552 X1 #1 SCREW EXTRACTOR & XL5H 5/64 LEFT HAND JOBBER DRIL
meta_title: CHAMPION 06552 X1 #1 SCREW EXTRACTOR & XL5H 5/64 LEFT HAND JOBBER DRIL
small_image_label: CHAMPION 06552 X1 #1 SCREW EXTRACTOR & XL5H 5/64 LEFT HAND JOBBER DRIL
thumbnail_label: CHAMPION 06552 X1 #1 SCREW EXTRACTOR & XL5H 5/64 LEFT HAND JOBBER DRIL
short_description:
Matching combination left hand industrial steel screw extractor and high speed steel twist drill
Made in the USA
Screw extractor spiral flute design
Brute Platinum twist drill avoids needing pilot hole, 135 degree split point
Use left hand twist drills in left hand rotation machinery
summary: Champion Cutting Tool ipac system provides you with professional grade cutting tool combinations of industrial steel screw extractor and Brute Platinum left hand high speed steel twist drill designed for electrical, plumbing, mechanical contracting, welding, machine shop and home maintenance. Brute Platinum XL5LH jobber length twist drills outperform standard "drill bits". You will get faster hole penetration and more holes per drill. Each twist drill is provided with a unique combination of premium high speed steel, geometries and NOMO (Nitride on Margin Only) surface treatment. This combination of treatment inables Brute Platinum twist drills to penetrate multiple 300 and 400 series stainless steel, austenitic stainless steel, mild and hardened titanium steel alloys, carbon steel and softer steel materials like copper alloys. Nitriding is the best substitute for cobalt drills and still has flexibility to avoid shattering. With the precision ground 135 degree split point tip there is no need to predrill pilot holes. Brute Platinum left hand twist drills will bit right into the material avoiding the walking effect in common 118 degree twist drills. Designed for use in left hand rotation multiple spindle, gear driven drilling heads, scew machine operations, lathes and any machinery with a left hand rotation. Left hand twist drills are also commonly used for drilling out broken or frozen bolts. The tapered web geometry in each twist drill provides faster penetration of the material. Our matching X1 industrial steel left hand, spiral flute, screw extractors are designed to remove broken screws, studs, bolts, or pipe fittings. The left hand rotation of the tapered flutes forces out almost any right hand threaded part. Recommended to be used with penetrating oil when removing rusty or corroded parts.
meta_keyword: CHAMPION 06552 X1 #1 SCREW EXTRACTOR & XL5H 5/64 LEFT HAND JOBBER DRIL

summary: Champion Cutting Tool ipac system provides you with professional grade cutting tool combinations of industrial steel screw extractor and Brute Platinum left hand high speed steel twist drill designed for electrical, plumbing, mechanical contracting, welding, machine shop and home maintenance. Brute Platinum XL5LH jobber length twist drills outperform standard "drill bits". You will get faster hole penetration and more holes per drill. Each twist drill is provided with a unique combination of premium high speed steel, geometries and NOMO (Nitride on Margin Only) surface treatment. This combination of treatment inables Brute Platinum twist drills to penetrate multiple 300 and 400 series stainless steel, austenitic stainless steel, mild and hardened titanium steel alloys, carbon steel and softer steel materials like copper alloys. Nitriding is the best substitute for cobalt drills and still has flexibility to avoid shattering. With the precision ground 135 degree split point tip there is no need to predrill pilot holes. Brute Platinum left hand twist drills will bit right into the material avoiding the walking effect in common 118 degree twist drills. Designed for use in left hand rotation multiple spindle, gear driven drilling heads, scew machine operations, lathes and any machinery with a left hand rotation. Left hand twist drills are also commonly used for drilling out broken or frozen bolts. The tapered web geometry in each twist drill provides faster penetration of the material. Our matching X1 industrial steel left hand, spiral flute, screw extractors are designed to remove broken screws, studs, bolts, or pipe fittings. The left hand rotation of the tapered flutes forces out almost any right hand threaded part. Recommended to be used with penetrating oil when removing rusty or corroded parts.

thumbnail_label: CHAMPION CM79-1 1^ ROTARY REBAR DRILL BIT 1/2^ SHANK CARBIDE TIPPED
short_description:
Rotary Rebar Cutters are carbide tipped and have a 1/2-Inch shank.
Easy drilling through embedded rebar and surrounding concrete.
Use in any 1/2-Inch capacity or larger drill motor with a three jaw chuck and no load speed of 440 rpm.
Application: Drill first with a hammer drill bit(1) until reaching rebar. Replace bit with CM79 drill then penetrate rebar(2). After completion of rebar drilling, complete drilling with hammer bit(3).
summary: CM79 Rebar Cutters are recommended for cutting through embedded reinforcing bar in concrete. Can be used in 1/2-Inch capacity or larger drill motor with "Jacobs style" chuck, with no-load speed of 440RPM.

summary:
Safety Hex Shank Bridge Reamers enlarge and align holes in structural steel
Rare earth magnets are embedded in hex shank for secure fit in electric and pneumatic tools & sockets to prevent injury on jobsites. Designed to comply with OSHA "Falling Object Protection Standard" OSHA 29 CFR Part 1926.760
Shank diameter of reamer matches socket size for bolt which will be driven through newly reamed hole
Left Hand Spiral and Right Hand Cut ejects chips forward for superior hole quality and operator safety
Ideal for use in bridge building, steel erection, ship building industries, and other structural steel applications
